    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "## Problem\n\nPath handling on Windows is inconsistent and buggy. Partly caused by Vim tech debt, partly by Neovim regressions.\n\n## Strategy\n\n\n- Always use `/` (forward slashes) internally. (Analogous to how we always use UTF-8 internally.) \n- On Windows, \n    - default to `/` slashes wherever possible, especially for cosmetic cases (buffer name, statusline, quickfix list, etc).\n    - convert to `\\` (backslash) only where required, for a limited set of *non-cosmetic* functions/features where the user explicitly requests/expects `\\` slashes.\n\n### \"Cosmetic\" cases where `/` slashes should always be enforced:\n\n- For options: the actual value (and everywhere it is displayed, e.g. `:set`). Even if the user sets `C:\\foo\\bar`, we store and display `C:/foo/bar`.\n- For buffers: in statusline, and anywhere else where mixed slashes was already possible. \n    - Example: if `bufname()` can return mixed slashes, then it's obviously safe for us to always return `/` slashes because there was never a guarantee of only `\\` slashes.\n\n### 'shellslash'\n\n'shellslash' is intended to make filenames compatible with Windows cmd.exe commands that don't support `/` slashes (usually because `/` is the \"switch\", like `-` on unix): `copy xcopy move del rename type more attrib dir xcopy robocopy attrib`\n\nFunctions which potentially should respect 'shellslash'\n\n```\nexepath\nexpand\nfnamemodify\nex_pwd ?\nf_chdir ?\nf_getcwd ?\n```\n\n### Documentation\n\n- `vim.uv` will continue to return `\\` slashes (we don't control it)\n\n\n## Plan\n\n- [x] step 1: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/37729\n- [x] followup: \n    - [x] should `vim_getenv` do `TO_SLASH` ? [ref](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/37729#discussion_r3138668328)\n    - [x] ❌ ~~drop TO_BACKSLASH for CreateProcessW arg0?~~ [ref] (https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/37729#discussion_r3139229341)\n    - [x] ❌ ~~do TO_SLASH in `expand_env` ? [ref](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/37729#discussion_r3139274919)~~ [rejected](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/39382#issuecomment-4328514446)\n- [ ] step 2:\n    - https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/39155\n    - https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/39426",
    "closed_at": null,
