        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> * [ ]  do TO_SLASH in `expand_env` ? [ref](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/37729#discussion_r3139274919) \n\nWhen I looked into this previously, I ran into some tricky cases. The main issue is that backslashe can be used as escape character, and since this is called from many places, I didn't find a good rule that handle them. It might be better to revisit this after we’ve done some of the other cleanup.\n\n> Functions which potentially should respect 'shellslash'\n\nFor now, PR #39155 might be a bit aggressive. I made these functions always return `/`, since I thought it would simplify things, i.e., nvim’s own functions always return `/`, while vim.uv functions return `\\`. But maybe users are used to these functions being affected by `shellslash`. :)",
